property_details: Elevate your Sarasota living experience at 1000 Boulevard of the Arts. With adventurous contemporary design, 1000 Boulevard of the Arts fuses sumptuous condominium residences with the vibrant atmosphere of the Hyatt Centric® Harborside boutique hotel. Perfectly positioned, residents will be immersed in waterfront vistas that stretch across The Quay harbor, The Bay park, and the coastal shoreline of Sarasota Bay. Living here means basking in resort-style amenities and the conveniences of a luxury hotel as part of your everyday life. For those seeking a spirited blend of excitement and sophistication, 1000 Boulevard of the Arts is the address of choice. This 20-level bayfront development designed by world-renowned SB Architects is home to 117 luxury residences. Residents arrive to a 24/7 staffed lobby and enjoy a choice of valet or self-parking. Here, attentive personal service is matched with an impressive array of private amenities. The 1- to 3-bedroom plus den residences range from 1,200 to over 3,000 sq. ft. and are now available at pre-construction pricing from $1.4 million.
amenity_details: From the moment residents arrive, 1000 Boulevard of the Arts makes an unforgettable impression. The dramatic covered arrival plaza and contemporary Grand Lobby, with a separate resident entrance and gathering space set the tone for an exceptional lifestyle. Beyond, an exclusive world of amenities unfolds, thoughtfully designed for relaxation, wellness, and effortless socializing. An extraordinary selection of indoor and outdoor spaces promotes wellness, connection, and enjoyment. The elevated Oasis Pool Deck, featuring comfortable cabanas, a spa, a fire pit lounge, BBQ grills, and inviting seating areas, offers the perfect setting to relax in the sun and take in the breathtaking views, along with the adjacent Splash Lounge. Residents and guests can gather in the spacious and elegantly appointed Club Room, which includes conversational seating areas, a catering kitchen, a bar, and an outdoor cocktail terrace. Completing the experience, a Private Dining Room boasts an impressive wine wall and a dedicated catering kitchen. Designed for both body and mind, the state-of-the-art Fitness Center at 1000 Arts features the latest high-performance exercise equipment and a glass-enclosed Movement Studio for personal training or group classes. The Hub offers an exclusive co-working environment with a variety of collaborative, private, and semi-private seating and meeting areas, while the Newsroom provides the day’s current world and finullcial news and papers in a casual, salon-style atmosphere with comfortable seating and daily coffee/beverage service. A 24/7 Staffed Lobby and On-site Property Management will control access to the luxury condo and provide concierge-style service ranging from everyday needs, such as dry cleaning, to pre-arrival residence preparation. Even four-legged residents are considered with a private, covered Dog Park and Spa, completing a vision of effortless, refined living at 1000 Boulevard of the Arts. At 1000 Boulevard of the Arts, ultra-private luxury condominium living is seamlessly woven into the high energy and services of the Hyatt Centric® Harborside. As a full-service luxury hotel, it provides the ultimate convenience of guest rooms for visiting family, additional meeting spaces, and a host of entertainment venues and events. Ground-level space for an independent restaurant will feature both indoor and outdoor seating to complete the resort-style ambiance.
developer_details: Based in Florida, Kolter Urban is redefining the landscape of residential development, consistently setting new benchmarks in luxury living and exceeding expectations for homebuyers and the industry alike. Guided by its mission of “Creating Better Communities,” Kolter brings over two decades of innovation and expertise to every project. This will be Kolter Urban’s sixth luxury condominium offering in Sarasota—having delivered VUE, Mark Sarasota, Bayso, and The Ritz-Carlton Residences, Sarasota, while currently selling The Ritz-Carlton Residences, Sarasota Bay—as well as the addition of a third full-service, branded hotel—the Hyatt Centric Harborside. With each home sold, Kolter Urban delivers more than a residence—it provides an elevated lifestyle enriched with thoughtfully designed amenities and premium finishes. The company remains committed to energy-efficient designs that seamlessly blend form and function. Having developed over $10 billion in residential projects—spanning completed and in-progress ventures—Kolter’s portfolio includes exceptional waterfront, water-view, and urban condominium residences that exemplify modern living in walkable, amenity-rich locations.
architect_details: For over 50 years, SB Architects has built a global reputation for excellence in the planning and design of large-scale hotels, resorts, destination communities, and their associated amenities, as well as multifamily residential and urban mixed-use developments. As a mid-size firm by design, SB Architects leverages the expertise of a seasoned team alongside the energy and vision of its second-generation leadership. Operating from offices in San Francisco and Miami, the firm is recognized as an industry leader for its collaborative approach, professionalism, and commitment to building strong client relationships. SB Architects combines global reach with hands-on dedication, delivering innovative, pragmatic solutions that set new benchmarks in design.
